snippet.textDisplay: Fully agree with everything - one of the few interviews where this happens for me.  I have no problem with them making a living or opting for a second home in Canada; I do however not want them to embarrass the Queen.  The Queen has been nothing but supportive of them both.  Some people seem to believe M had her own platform already when this is simply not true, she now has a platform because of her royal status and for no other reasons, she is famous for marrying PH.  I seriously doubt people would have any interest in her at all had she never married H.  Of course they should keep the Royal and their titles, H was born into the RF, but what they shouldn't do is profit from this personally, I don't think this needs spelling out to H at all, it's obviously M that doesn't question the ethics here.  Clearly she thought she would cash in, for charity and doing good yes, but also because she wants a nice big slice of the cake for herself in the process.  My problem is how she pleads her innocence and plays the victim, to try and disguise her motives, she may be able to pull the wool over H's eyes,  but a large number of people can now see what she is all about, people are annoyed because of how she behaves and for no other reasons - of course we all wished them well and hoped it would work out; but the cracks have now appeared.  This latest tweet is another example of what winds us up.  If there was ever a person that should stay off SM it is M.  Sadly, I think this will play out for sometime yet, but it will end in divorce once the illusion falls away for H, when he gets tired of trying to keep her happy and finds himself in disagreement more and more with what she wants.  The nation loves PH, understandably we have our concerns and feel passionately about this - even though in reality it effects us in no other ways.
